  h2.under 1) Taleb's social proof
  p Publishers say bestsellers need endorsements from highbrow media.
  //- p Nassim Taleb disagreed. He argued that readers connect with other readers better.
  p Nassim Taleb disagreed. For his latest book he replaced praise from!{' '}
    span.italic Economist et al.
    |!{' '}with words from real readers.
  p Unsurprisingly it was a bestseller.
  p Readers connect with readers in a way Forbes et al. can't.
  p Nothing realer than your readers own words.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/rs2.png" alt="Passive voice").img__100
  h2.under 2) Patagonia's images
  p In the 1980's all outdoor fashion catalogs looked the same.
  p Paid models. Fake hikes.
  p Patagonia’s founder, Yvon Chouinard, was sick of it. So he placed a note in their catalog asking customers to send in real photos.
  p Suddenly Patagonia stood out. They still only use real customers today.
  p.inwardSpeech A real surfer showing a little skin is a lot sexier than a half-dressed, anonymous model — Yvon Chouinard
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/rs3.jpg" alt="Passive voice").img__100
  h2.under 3) Rihanna's copy
  p Most product launches feel like a copy and paste job.
  p Look what happens when Rihanna drops the clichés and talks like a real person.
  //- p When Rihanna launched!{' '}
  //-   span.italic Fenty Skin
  //-   |!{' '}she dropped the clichés and added some personality.
  //- p But look what happens when Rihanna drops the clichés and remembers her personality.
  //- p And actually sounded like...!{' '}
  //-   span.italic Rihanna
  //-   | !
  //- p Most product launches sound like LinkedIn autocomplete.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/rs4.png" alt="Passive voice").img__100
  h2.under 4) People's Vote Ads
  p The!{' '}
    span.italic People's Vote
    |!{' '}Campaign spent more than £800k in the lead up to the 2019 UK election. Fancy cameras, expensive lighting, celebrities etc...
  p Their best performing ad? Staff talking to an iPhone on their way to work.
  video(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/rs1.mp4" class="img__55" playsinline="playsinline" poster="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/rs5.jpg" onclick="this.paused ? this.play() : this.pause();")
  h2.under 5) Chanel's drawings
  p Chanel asked employee's kids to hand draw products for Mother's Day.
  p Much!{' '}
    span.italic realer
    |!{' '}than the superficial BS we're accustomed to.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/rs6.png" alt="Passive voice").img__100
  h2.under 6) Beachbody's ads
  p Real ads feels like regular content.
  p Contrast these two ads from Beachbody's CEO.
  p The first is your classic ad. Clean cut. On script. The second feels more like a fitness vlog. Dropping sweat. Off-the-cuff.
  p Much more authentic.
